  "title": "MANAGER",
  "description": "<ul><li><li>Your main responsibility is to lead the development and implementation of marketing campaigns, including:</li><li>Develop marketing campaign ideas, objectives, budgets, and execution calendar.</li><li>Conduct brand building activities such as events, PR, and social media.</li><li>Maintain constant brand presence across all key channels and consumer touch points.</li><li>Track and monitor brand and competitor activities and performance metrics.</li><li>Track and monitor campaign performance metrics.</li><li>Develop and manage brand and marketing assets.</li><li>Manage external relationships with freelancers and other creative support.</li></li><li><strong>SKILLS & EXPERIENCE</strong></li><li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills at all levels in the organisation and proven ability to build strong professional relationships.</li><li>Highly organised and able to multi-task</li><li>Proven experience in creating and executing detailed partner marketing plans.</li><li>Systematic approach to sharing knowledge and best practices across multiple teams.</li><li>Analytical tendencies with a natural curiosity to measure, test, learn and iterate to get the best results possible.</li><li>Strong project management skills</li><li>6 days working/ week</li><li>Able to work at the weekend and public holiday and night shift</li></li></ul>",
